item.title: The First Person to Hack the iPhone Built a Self-Driving Car. In His Garage.
item.description:
The First Person to Hack the iPhone Built a Self-Driving Car. In His Garage.

From A few days before Thanksgiving, George Hotz, a 26-year-old hacker, invites me to his house in San Francisco to check out a project he's been working on. He says it's a self-driving car that he had built in about a month. The claim seems absurd.

item.title: Iskraemeco :: Big, smart plans for SEC in Saudi Arabia
item.description:
Iskraemeco :: Big, smart plans for SEC in Saudi Arabia

55,000 smart meters that Iskraemeco will start supplying to SEC at the end of 2015 are a clear signal that the country is following its set plans. The specifics of the countries` topology require the meters to be highly efficient in an environment, characterised by high temperatures and a high humidity level.
